she said. `` But ... how could she say on there that I know the law and I disregarded it. It's crazy. The report by Ms. <PERSON> Geivers </PERSON> acknowledged that Ms. <PERSON> DeSillers </PERSON> had suffered a `` great personal tragedy'' with her son's death. But it added `` she appears to have ignored the laws ... when it suited her purposes to do so.'' Ms. <PERSON> DeSillers </PERSON> has said the questionable expenditures were necessary to raise money for an organ donation awareness program. She said some of the money went to help her keep up a `` professional appearance'' while soliciting funds as president of the now-dormant <ORGANIZATION> Ronnie </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> DeSillers </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Foundation </ORGANIZATION>. And she said the jewelry expense was to buy back items she had pawned to pay <PERSON> Ronnie </PERSON>'s medical expenses and payments to her brother and boyfriend <PERSON> Jose </PERSON> <PERSON> Castillo </PERSON> were to repay loans. `` <PERSON> Jose </PERSON> spent more than twice that helping <PERSON> Ronnie </PERSON> and I,'' she said. `` He lost two businesses when he came to <LOCATION> Pittsburgh </LOCATION>.''
