 T spokesman <PERSON> Herb </PERSON> <PERSON> Linnen </PERSON> said the timing of the company's proposal was coincidental to the <ORGANIZATION> FCC </ORGANIZATION>'s preparations this week for another step toward radically changing the way <ORGANIZATION> AT </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; T is regulated The <ORGANIZATION> FCC </ORGANIZATION> on Thursday is expected to unveil a specific proposal to put in place a new system of regulating <ORGANIZATION> AT </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; T by capping rates rather than profits. <ORGANIZATION> AT </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; T has been lobbying hard for the change.
